Residents and farmers of Newcastle in KwaZulu-Natal have taken to the streets to protest rural killings. Courtesy of #DStv403 NEWCASTLE - Residents and farmers of Newcastle in KwaZulu-Natal have taken to the streets to protest rural killings. The protest follows the double-murder of Glen Rafferty and his wife Vida last week. READ: Cele to visit KZN following murders Police Minister Bheki Cele has promised that swift action will be taken. Deputy President David Mabuza has condemned farm attacks and called for a meeting with the Inter-Ministerial Committee on Land Reform and Agriculture on Friday to discuss interventions to curb violence on farms.